Package de.server.controller.userAndSelfServiceStand

Class SelfServiceStandController

java.lang.Object
de.server.controller.userAndSelfServiceStand.SelfServiceStandController
@RestController @RequestMapping("/selfServiceStand") public class SelfServiceStandController extends Object
With the help of this class, a new self-service stand can be created, deleted, and a user list can be output.

  • Method Details

    • addUser

      @PostMapping("/addUser/") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<?> addUser​(@RequestBody SelfServiceStandRequest selfServiceStandRequest)
      This method adds an existing user to an already existing self-service stand. The user who adds a user must have admin rights. Every user cannot be added to self-service statuses that have the same name.
      Returns:
      message and httpStatus

    • removeUser

      @DeleteMapping("/removeUser/{removeUserName}/{userName}/{selfServiceStandName}") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<?> removeUser​(@PathVariable String removeUserName, @PathVariable String userName, @PathVariable String selfServiceStandName)
      This function removes a user from an existing self-service stand. The user who removes this must have admin rights.
      Parameters:
      removeUserName - The name of the user to be removed.
      userName - The name of the user which one user removes.
      selfServiceStandName - The self-service-stand name.
      Returns:
      message and httpStatus

    • createSelfServiceStand

      @PostMapping("/{userName}/{selfServiceStandName}") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<?> createSelfServiceStand​(@PathVariable String selfServiceStandName, @PathVariable String userName)
      This method creates a new self-service booth and adds the user. The user receives admin rights.
      Parameters:
      selfServiceStandName - The self-servie-stand name.
      userName - The user name.
      Returns:
      message and httpStatus

    • getListOfUser

      @GetMapping("/{selfServiceStandName}") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<List<User>> getListOfUser​(@PathVariable String selfServiceStandName)
      This method provides a list of users who belong to the self-service stand.
      Parameters:
      selfServiceStandName - The self-service-stand name.
      Returns:
      A list with users.
